    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden text-content text-secondary"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>YouTube is a great service for storing and managing your videos. While this is handy, many people want to be able to display their videos within their own website as well. In this tutorial we'll see how the Media, Media Internet Sources, and Media: YouTube modules can help give you a nice, seamless way to integrate YouTube videos into your site, and give really nice control over how those videos look, along with some built-in media management tools.</p>
